## Invariants

- **Admin custom UI:** Follow [Custom components — overview](https://payloadcms.com/docs/custom-components/overview), register paths under `admin.components` / field `admin.components`, run **`pnpm generate:importmap`** — see `payload-custom-components.mdc`.
- **Relations:** Generated types use `number \| Doc` (or similar). Treat **ID vs populated** explicitly: use **`depth`** / **`populate`** for nested data, or **narrow** in components (`typeof x === 'object' && x !== null` before field access).
- **REST / `fetch`:** Response bodies are **`unknown`** until validated or asserted at the boundary—same as Payload’s REST contract: **type at the edge**, not `any` throughout.
- **`getPayload`:** Payload 3 caches the instance; **do not** add a second module-level cache in `getPayload.ts`.

## Anti-patterns

- Editing only React components when the **schema or depth** is what changed.
- Assuming **`slug` queries** return populated relations without setting **`depth`**.
- **Skipping** `generate:types` after collection/field/plugin changes.

If ambiguous, open the matching overview link first, then implement.

**Topic rules:** `.cursor/rules/payload-*.mdc` — start from **`payload-features-overview.mdc`** (features), **`payload-ecosystem.mdc`** (plugins, commerce, examples, integrations), and **`payload-deployment.mdc`** (production: build without DB, deploy, abuse, performance links) for the overview URL ↔ rule map; then hooks, queries, folders/trash/presets, **admin** + **admin-ui-surfaces**, custom components, local-api-advanced, docs-support, plus APIs, auth, Lexical, storage, preview, versions, jobs, email, migrations, i18n, TypeScript, plugins, security, performance, multi-tenant, ecommerce, forms. Regenerate generated rules from `scripts/generate-payload-cursor-rules.mjs`: `pnpm generate:cursor-rules:payload` (**does not** overwrite `payload-basics.mdc`).
